Project: Simple web server using Express to listen at port 8080
const express = require("express"); (import express)
const app = express(); (server application is created)
app.get("/", (req, res) => {
res.send("Hello, World!");
}); (if someone visits homepage (/), respond Hello World)


app.listen(8080, () => {
console.log("Server is running on http://localhost:8080");
}); )(start server and make it listen on port 8080) console.log is a callback function that runs when server starts
Use postman to test get, post, delete

Step 2 - Then run node . in terminal to start server

Callback is a function that is passed into another function to be executed later 
The callback only runs after Express successfully starts listening

JSON- Javascript  Object Notation is used to store and exchange structured data between servers, apps and APIs

Middleware is a function that runs before your request reaches the final route. It reads incoming JSON and converts it for server to use. It is used for security checks, authentication, login reqs

Step 3 - Create Dockerfile
FROM node:20 (use node environment)
WORKDIR/app (set folder inside container)
COPY package.json (copy dependencies file)
RUN npm install (install packages)
COPY .. (copy my code)
EXPOSE 8080 (open port 8080)
CMD (start my app)
Step 4 - Build Image
docker build -t student-api .

Step 5 - Run Container
docker run -p 8080:8080 student-api (host port:container port)

